<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#8F9CAC"><tr><td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="8" bgcolor="#ffffff"><tr><td>
<font class="title">Guild Charter</font><br><font class="content"><br><br><br><br><p align="justify">Please read these rules thoroughly and carefully.<br />
If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to ask an officer in game.<p><br />
</p><br><p align="justify"><b><u><big>Member Pledge:</big></b></u><p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To always uphold all guild rules and beliefs, both written and 
implied.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To treat other players with as much or more respect than I wish to be shown.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To use the proper methods for problem resolution, including, but not 
limited to: compromise, escalation to guild officers, and as a last 
resort, 
involving a Game Master.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To understand that walking away from a conflict is sometimes the best 
resolution.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To always act as though my entire Guild?s reputation rides on my 
every 
action ? because it does.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To assist my fellow Dark Rain Members to the best of my ability.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To never ask more from others than I am willing to sacrifice myself.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To regularly visit the website and forums. I cannot complain if I do 
not 
take advantage of all channels of communication.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To abide by any decisions made by an officer.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To do my Best to make Dark Rain the best guild I can.<p>
<br>
<br>


<b><u><big>Officer Pledge:</b></u></i></big><br>
<i>As a Dark Rain Officer, in addition to the Member Pledges, I pledge:</i><p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To make myself available to my fellow Dark Rain Members ? not to the 
detriment of your group or of the raid, but to be available when I can.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To act as a role model for others to follow.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To be fair and impartial when resolving disputes.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To communicate effectively and regularly with my fellow officers and 
members.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To resolve a problem to the best of my ability as soon as it is 
discovered, or take the necessary steps to escalate the issue.
· To step back and cool off when necessary. If emotions are running 
high, a 
resolution will be harder to come to.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To do my best to make Dark Rain the best guild I can. (Yes, it is in 
here 
twice for an Officer)<p>
<br>
<br>
<b><u><big>Mistress Pledge:</b></u></big><br>
<i>As your Guild Mistress, I pledge, in addition to the Member Pledge and 
the 
Officer Pledge:</i><p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> To make time for each member to get to know something about them.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To know my Officers well enough to know how hard I can push before 
getting 
pushed back.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To always listen.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To always make decisions with the Guild?s well-being first and 
foremost in 
mind.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To take time for myself so I can remain fresh and excited about Dark 
Rain.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To delegate what I can so I do not become bogged down in the details, 
and 
miss the fun stuff.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To choose my Officers with care.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To work to resolve any problems as soon as I am aware of them.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To tell my Guild Members I appreciate them, if not in game when it 
happens, then on the forums.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To do whatever it takes to make Dark Rain the guild we all know it 
can be.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To never pull rank unless there is no other option.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To admit that I am sometimes wrong.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> To ask for help when I need it.<p>
<br>
<br>

<b><u><big>Officer Rules:</b></u></big><p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> All Officers are required to read the forums at least 3 times a week.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> All Officers are to put the well being of the guild first and 
foremost 
when making decisions.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> All Officers are to bring a problem to the attention of the Guild 
Mistress and fellow Officers as soon as the problem is discovered. 
Silence 
helps no one.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> All Officers are to recognize within themselves their breaking 
point, and 
as soon as you feel you are losing control, turn to a fellow officer 
for 
help. It is NOT a sign of weakness to ask for help. The Guild ALWAYS 
comes 
first. If you do not feel capable of handling a situation, and there is 
a 
fellow Officer online that can help, Ask them for help. Even if all you 
need 
is to vent.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> There will be times when a member will talk to you in confidence. 
You are 
expected to keep that confidence, as long as it does not harm the guild 
in 
any way.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> If you disagree with a fellow Officer or the Guild Mistress, use an 
appropriate means of communicating this. Most of the time, this will 
mean 
take it to tells.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> Under NO circumstances do I EVER want to see remarks to one another 
in 
guild chat that are meant to belittle the other?s authority. If you 
can?t 
show respect for each other, how can we ask our members to respect us?<p> 
<strong><big>·</strong></big> These rules will be amended and refined as we grow.<p>
<br>
<br>

<b><u><big>Loot Rules</b></u></big><p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> If you bring 2 chars to a raid, only your ?Main? will be eligible for 
loots, 
unless the item will otherwise rot.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> You may only receive loot for the character in attendance.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> When an item drops, the Main Loot will announce the loot, if you wish 
to 
have that piece, you say ?aye? in /gu or /ooc, whichever channel is 
designated for that. This requires you MUST pay attention at all times. 
If 
you miss the announcement of the loot and don?t say AYE, then you will 
not 
be considered for that item.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> The Main Loot then decides who receives the loot based on the following 
criteria:<p>
<b>Use</b> - Will you use the gear full time, as resist gear, or do you plan 
to 
sell it?<p>
<b>Stats</b> - Is it an upgrade to what you currently have?
Class - a high AC belt will be of more use to the guild if a warrior is 
wearing it as opposed to a caster.<p>
<b>Raid Attendance</b> - Do you only show up for raids that benefit you or do 
you 
come to all raids you canto help the guild as a whole?<p>
<b>Level</b> - In the rare case that all other criteria are equal, the higher 
level 
will be awarded the loot.<p>

<br>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> The Decision of the Main Loot is final, and can only be overridden by 
the 
GuildMistress.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Once you are awarded a drop, you will not be awarded another drop this 
raid 
until all others have received something, unless you are the only 
choice and 
the loot will otherwise rot.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> /ran will be used at the Main Loot?s discretion.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Once you receive an item, it is yours. However, if you get a 
replacement on 
a future raid, and the original item is droppable, I?d like to see you 
donate the item back to the guild to be re-awarded to make the guild 
stronger as a whole.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Items that are not awarded will be available for sale through the guild 
bank 
at a reduced price. If. After a certain period of time, no member 
expresses 
interest in purchasing the item, it will be sold and the funds added to 
the 
guild account.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Gems that drop will go to the guild. Cash gems are sold to finance 
raids, 
events, etc. Quest gems will be sold to members for 50pp, in the case 
of 
Velious gems, or a reasonable discounted price in the case of other 
gems. 
You can also exchange a Velious quest gem you have for one the guild 
has.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Epic Loot: Raids for Epic loot are usually organized with a specific 
member 
in mind. In the case of an unplanned epic drop, the piece will be 
awarded to 
the individual present that is furthest along in their epic.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Spells or Songs that drop will be held for guild members use at no 
charge to 
the member. Spells that can not be used by any member?s main character 
will 
be sold for 10pp to a member for an alt, or for current market value in 
NFP.<p>
<br>
<br>

<b><u>Definitions:</b></u><p>

<b>Main Character:</b> the Character that was recruited into Dark Rain. If I 
tagged 
your Shaman first, that is your main, even if your Warrior is higher 
and 
comes into the guild later. In the case you bring two characters of 
similar 
levels into the guild at the same time, your main will be identified at 
that 
time.<p>

<b>Main Loot:</b> Each Raid, 1 officer will be designated Main Loot. This 
announcement will be made at the beginning of the raid so you know who 
to 
listen to if you want what just dropped.<p>

<b>Epic Loot</b> - any piece that is a required component for a class epic.<p>

<b>Cash Gems</b> - all gems which are NOT for a quest nor can be made into 
resist 
jewelry. Cash gems are sold to vendors.<p>

<b>Velious Quest Gems</b> - all gems which are required components for the 
Velious 
Quest Armor.<p>

<b>Current Market Value:</b> Determined by the Guild Finance Officer at the 
time of 
the sale.<p>
<br>
<br>

<b><u><big>Raids:</b></u></big><p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> Any guild event that is planned in advance and requires more than 1 
group to attend. Hate is a guild raid. 2 groups agreeing to go to 
Maiden?s 
Eye to hunt that night is NOT a guild event, therefore not subject to 
these 
rules. A pick up group in Seb of all Dark Rain members is NOT a guild 
event. 
If all members agree, these rules can be used in pick up groups or for 
hunting parties.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> Raid start and end times are set in advance as early as possible. 
Please 
plan on attending the entire raid. Coming late and /or leaving early 
causes 
disruption and can endanger the entire raid party.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Most raids are NOT going to be Experience Raids. Any talk of 
experience, 
either that you are getting some, you aren't getting any, you are the 
KS 
group, you want to be in the KS group, etc, is forbidden during a raid. 
It 
serves no purpose whatsoever other than to cause hard feelings. You 
WILL be 
asked to leave if you tell everyone how much experience you are getting 
in 
your group. You can also expect that when groups are made in the 
future, you 
will NOT be in that group again.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Not everyone will get something each raid - the loot rules are 
designed 
to encourage regular raid attendance.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Some zones have better drops for certain classes. Don?t Whine when 
one 
character happens to get three drops that day. I am sure there are 
plenty of 
raids where that person got nothing.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Assist the Main Tank. All Members should have /assist MT hot keys 
made 
before the raid starts. All raids will have time in the beginning to 
test 
your hot keys, make sure there are in the right chat channel, etc.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Everyone is expected to KNOW who the Main Tank is, and who the 
Secondary 
Assist it. ONLY Main Tank (or secondary) should break mez. While accidents do 
happen, a mez broken early equals the death of the mezzer, which could 
very 
well spell wipe out. Violation of mezz rules could end up in you being 
asked 
to leave raid. Repeated violations will result in you being removed 
from 
Dark Rain. This is THAT important.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Dark Rain encourages our members to enjoy each other. HOWEVER, there 
is a 
time and a place for everything. Gathering for a raid, the buffing 
process, 
etc, is NOT the time for duels and horseplay. We need to have our game 
faces 
on; let?s get in and get the job done. We can fool around later. 
Violations 
of this policy will result in anything from a verbal warning to raid 
and /or 
guild removal. I will not risk the success of the raid on any one 
person.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Unless we raid Crushbone, I expect all members to conduct themselves 
like 
characters that have been played well for 50+ levels. Ask questions 
EARLY if 
you have them. We would rather answer the same question about that trap 
on 
the bridge 5 times than spend an hour getting you out once. If EVER in 
doubt, ask. Chances are there are others with the same questions.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Raids are NOT the appropriate situations to discuss other guild 
business. Do not send the raid leader or your Officers tells unless 
they are 
needed for the raid. All officers have a role in each raid, whether it 
is 
seen by the members or not. We all know all it takes is one second of 
distraction for someone to die. Your concerns about Dark Rain are 
important, 
but not during a raid.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Raids can be suggested and led by anyone wishing to do so. Utilize 
the 
forums to get the process started.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> All Raid Attendees are expected to do SOME research on the zone we 
are 
going to. You should have printed maps If available), know what kinds 
of 
mobs we will be fighting, know if any drops will be for you. I NEVER 
want to 
hear ?Does anything drop here for my class?? You are all over level 45. 
You 
are not expected to be an expert, but at least take 10 minutes to read 
up on 
our target on the websites. If you have cool information about that 
zone, 
post it in the forums for all of us to share!<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Most Dark Rain raids are open to friends. Let the raid leader know 
as 
soon as you know they are coming. All friends are required to attend 3 
Dark 
Rain raids before they are eligible for loot. (Unless the item will 
otherwise rot or can?t be used by Dark Rain). It is my belief that by 
the 
third raid, they are a member of Dark Rain, if not by tag, at least in 
spirit.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Dark Rain will attempt to help port everyone to and from the raid. 
HOWEVER, if you log in 5 mins before the raid is set to begin, don?t 
expect 
one of us to drop from our groups and come get you. If time will be an 
issue, log near the raid site the night before. If you know you will 
need a 
port and/or help getting to the raid site, please plan on being at a 
druid 
ring/wiz port 30 mins before raid time. Our druids and wizards have 
enough 
to do for themselves without having to spend an hour zoning.
<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big>  In the case of a massive Corpse Run, please reserve guild chat for 
CR 
communication only. Your Officers will ask you to reserve this channel 
when 
it is required. Otherwise, it's business as normal in chat!<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Your Raid Officers are juggling many things at once on a raid. 
Please 
know they are working for the betterment of the guild, and sometimes we 
will 
not have time to chat with you. We may even get a little short 
inadvertently. Please forgive us now, and have patience. WE will be 
your 
loving friends again as soon as the raid is over. This is NOT excusing 
anyone for rude behavior during a raid or at any time. This is saying I may not laugh at your witty banter while I am making groups. I still 
laughed, 
but I didn?t type lol.. This is NOT saying please forgive me for 
cussing at 
you and yelling. That is not acceptable behavior, and will not be 
tolerated.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> There will be times when we will get very frustrated. At that 
point, it 
will be your job to keep spirits up. The worse thing that can happen is 
we 
all get down at once. If you notice the stress level of your friend 
seems a 
little high, do what you can to help them take a step back and breath. 
This 
is Supposed to be fun!!!<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> These rules are subject to be amended and refined as we go.
<br>
<br>

<b><u><big>Guild Rules:</b></u></big><p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Members must be at least level <b>50</b> to join.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Each member may have 2 alts tagged Dark Rain. Each alt must be /role 
unless they are 50 or over.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Each member is strongly encouraged to have an alt tagged DR for ease 
of 
communication during raids in the case of a wipeout.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> All Guild Members are to act right. You know how to behave, you know 
what 
is right and what is wrong. If you are in doubt, it is probably wrong!<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> Each member is expected to respect the other member's time and 
resources. 
Druids and Wizzys are not your personal taxis, clerics are not your 
personal rez machines, etc.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> Each member is expected to help out your fellow members in whichever 
way 
you can. This does not mean leaving a tent group in Velks to go group 
with 
someone on the moon UNLESS you want to!<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> Guild Members are encouraged to group together, but not required. 
Pick up 
groups are often a necessity in this game.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> All members are required to read the forums at least once a week. 
Too 
much happens on the forums for you to not read them.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Each member is required to show respect to every other member of 
Dark 
Rain. This includes name calling, teasing, flirting, etc. What you 
think is 
harmless fun can be quite upsetting to the recipient.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> Each Member is expected to speak up when they see a problem. All 
Officers are available to listen to you. Do not expect an officer to 
drop 
everything to speak with you, but know as soon as they are safe and 
able to 
talk with you, they will. If you don?t tell us there is a problem, we 
can 
not fix it.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Every member has the responsibility to make this guild the 
strongest 
they can. You know your strengths. Use them for good, not evil.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> Members are FORBIDDEN from harassing other players. You will be 
warned 
once by an officer, next time, you will be reported to a GM. Harassment 
includes: Name Calling, Teasing, Flirting, Unwanted Sexual Innuendos, 
Racial 
Comments (RL and In Game). It is harassment if it makes one party 
uncomfortable in any way.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> If you feel you are being harassed, ask the offender to stop 
immediately, in clear words. If they do not stop, report them to an 
officer. 
Once the officer has relayed to you that the harassment should stop, 
and the 
offender continues, report them to Verant for harassment and let the 
chips 
fall where they may. You are NOT expected to put up with that behavior 
just 
because they share a tag with you, and trust me, they will not share 
that 
tag for very long.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> All of these rules are subject to the interpretation of the officer 
at 
the time the rule is being enforced.<p>

<strong><big>·</strong></big> A member can be detagged by an officer for violating certain rules, 
their actions will be judged at the time. In most cases, 2 officers 
will be 
required to agree to detag the individual. There will be circumstances, 
however, that an officer is forced to make that decision alone. The 
decision 
should always have the well being of the guild as a whole first and 
foremost 
in mind.<p>
<strong><big>·</strong></big> These rules will be amended as need arises.<p>



<b><big>Thank you for reading these rules, We look forward to hearing from you.<p>
Good Journeys,<p>

The Dark Rain Leadership.<p></p><br><p align="justify"></p><br><br><br><br><br><center> </center><br><br><p align="right">Dark Rain</p><p align="right">Copyright &copy; by . All Right Reserved.</p></font><table width="100%"><tr><td><a href="modules.php?name=Content&file=printpage&pid=2"><img src="images/print.gif" border="0"Alt="_PRINTER" width="15" height="11"> Print this page</a></td><td><div align="right"><font class="tiny">Published on: 2002-03-13 (427 reads)</div></td></tr></table></font></p><center>[ <a href="javascript:history.go(-1)">Go Back</a> ]</center></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
